https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/dsa/longest-consecutive-sequence-binary-tree/

class Solution {
    private int maxLen = 0;
    public int longestConsecutive(TreeNode root) {
        if (root == null) return 0;
        dfs(root, root.val, 0);
        return maxLen;
    }
    private void dfs(TreeNode node, int expected, int currLen) {
        if (node == null) return;
        if (node.val == expected) 
            currLen++;
         else 
            currLen = 1;
        maxLen = Math.max(maxLen, currLen);
        dfs(node.left, node.val + 1, currLen);
        dfs(node.right, node.val + 1, currLen);
    }
}


Time & Space Complexity
• 	Time: O(n), where n is the number of nodes
• 	Space: O(h), where h is the height of the tree (due to recursion)
